<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            Consulate General at Batavia</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v06</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d813</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">813</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-08-04T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-08-04T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-04T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="813" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d813">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856E.00/8–447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Consulate General at Batavia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">u. s. urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_Niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-04T18:00:00-04:00">August 4, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>209. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 204.<note n="79" xml:id="d813fn79">Same as telegram 380, August 1, 7 p.m., <ref target="#pg_1004">p.
                            1004</ref>.</note> We have offered our good offices to the Netherlands
                    and desire, of course, to make them available to Indonesians also but are
                    somewhat at loss how this can be done. Emissaries of <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>s have been reported in various countries<note n="80" xml:id="d813fn80">Telegram 955, August 8, 10 a.m., from Cairo, reported that
                        two Indonesians, Soetan Sjahrir and Hadji Agus Salim, left August 7 for New
                        York as delegates to the United Nations (501.BC/8–847).</note> while some
                    members <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Govt understood in Batavia. We
                    have no <gloss target="#t_Info1">info</gloss> re authority any these officials,
                    however, and in circumstances leave your discretion means conveying offer good
                    offices <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Govt.</p>
                <p>Would appreciate your advice whether Batavia or elsewhere best spot undertake
                    negotiations implementation good offices. Please comment <pb facs="1027" n="1013" xml:id="pg_1013"/> also as to willingness and capacity both sides
                    carry out US recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
